<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1554,2020]" lastBlockId="2.[151,1437,152,1820]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="3" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
Head small, distinctly narrower than pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[713,779,1554,1580]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="14.[151,255,1718,1742]" captionTargetBox="[200,1387,311,1657]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[167,1413,277,1692]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 1. Cyrta hirsuta A, head and thorax, dorsal view; B, face; C, connective and aedeagus, lateral view; D, male genital capsule, lateral view; E, style and connective, dorsal view; F, apex of aedeagus, ventral view; G, valve and style, ventral view; H, base of aedeagus and dorsal connective, anteroventral view; I, male genital capsule, dorsal view; J, aedeagus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/182577/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
Fig. 
<number box="[768,779,1554,1580]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
A). Vertex shorter or slightly longer than width between eyes; anterior margin rounded, sloping to front; posterior margin slightly concave; coronal suture distinct, extending nearly to anterior margin. Ocelli on vertex, near anterior margin, situated approximately their own diameters from corresponding eye. Face similar in length to width; lateral frontal suture extending well beyond corresponding ocellus; transclypeal suture indistinct; anteclypeus broadening apically, apical margin slightly convex, usually with pair of stout setae; gena flat; lora broad; rostrum long, about two thirds of anteclypeus; labrum about two thirds of labium; antenna about as long as body, arising adjacent to midpoint of inner margin of eye; antennal ledge indistinct; antennal pit shallow (
<figureCitation box="[944,1011,1834,1860]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="14.[151,255,1718,1742]" captionTargetBox="[200,1387,311,1657]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[167,1413,277,1692]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 1. Cyrta hirsuta A, head and thorax, dorsal view; B, face; C, connective and aedeagus, lateral view; D, male genital capsule, lateral view; E, style and connective, dorsal view; F, apex of aedeagus, ventral view; G, valve and style, ventral view; H, base of aedeagus and dorsal connective, anteroventral view; I, male genital capsule, dorsal view; J, aedeagus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/182577/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
Fig. 
<number box="[999,1011,1834,1860]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
B). Pronotum about 
<number box="[1251,1289,1834,1860]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="2.5">2.5</number>
~ 
<date box="[1304,1340,1834,1860]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
<number box="[1304,1317,1834,1860]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="3.0">3</number>
X
</date>
broader than median length; posterior margin slightly concave; lateral margin long with carina present, curved to eye anteriorly (
<figureCitation box="[280,346,1914,1940]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="14.[151,255,1718,1742]" captionTargetBox="[200,1387,311,1657]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[167,1413,277,1692]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 1. Cyrta hirsuta A, head and thorax, dorsal view; B, face; C, connective and aedeagus, lateral view; D, male genital capsule, lateral view; E, style and connective, dorsal view; F, apex of aedeagus, ventral view; G, valve and style, ventral view; H, base of aedeagus and dorsal connective, anteroventral view; I, male genital capsule, dorsal view; J, aedeagus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/182577/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
Fig. 
<number box="[335,346,1914,1940]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
A). Scutellum slightly longer than pronotum; basal width similar to width of head; transverse depression somewhat indistinct; posterior half weakly elevated and inclined from transverse suture; posterolateral ledge indistinct; tufts of hairlike setae present or absent on lateral margin (
<figureCitation box="[1097,1163,1994,2020]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="14.[151,255,1718,1742]" captionTargetBox="[200,1387,311,1657]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[167,1413,277,1692]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 1. Cyrta hirsuta A, head and thorax, dorsal view; B, face; C, connective and aedeagus, lateral view; D, male genital capsule, lateral view; E, style and connective, dorsal view; F, apex of aedeagus, ventral view; G, valve and style, ventral view; H, base of aedeagus and dorsal connective, anteroventral view; I, male genital capsule, dorsal view; J, aedeagus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/182577/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
Fig. 
<number box="[1152,1163,1994,2020]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
A). Forewing with five apical cells; middle and outer subapical cells closed, inner subapical cell open; claval veins connected by crossvein to each other and to claval suture; appendix broad with margin rounded, extended to fourth apical cell; claval margin strongly elevated and crimped at apex. 
<collectingCountry box="[834,893,232,258]" name="India" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Hind</collectingCountry>
wing venation complete. Legs densely setose. Fore femur with setae short to long: anterior surface with intercalary (IC) setae irregularly arranged and anteromedial (AM) setae long (
<figureCitation box="[467,539,312,338]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="15.[151,255,1670,1694]" captionTargetBox="[181,1402,236,1616]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[172,1426,194,1646]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 2. Cyrta hornei A, fore femur, anterior surface; B, fore femur, dorsal surface; C, fore femur, ventral surface; D, fore tibia, anterior surface; E, fore tibia, dorsal surface; F, fore tibia, ventral surface. G, apex of hind femur, dorsal view; H, base of hind tibia, dorsal surface." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/182578/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
Fig. 
<number box="[523,539,312,338]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
A); dorsal surface with dense setae from base to apex, irregularly arranged, length of setae gradually increased apically, several very short anterodorsal (AD) setae basally (
<figureCitation box="[1270,1340,352,378]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="15.[151,255,1670,1694]" captionTargetBox="[181,1402,236,1616]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[172,1426,194,1646]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 2. Cyrta hornei A, fore femur, anterior surface; B, fore femur, dorsal surface; C, fore femur, ventral surface; D, fore tibia, anterior surface; E, fore tibia, dorsal surface; F, fore tibia, ventral surface. G, apex of hind femur, dorsal view; H, base of hind tibia, dorsal surface." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/182578/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
Fig. 
<number box="[1324,1340,352,378]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
B); ventral surface with anteroventral (AV) setae long, posteroventral (PV) setae dense and irregularly arranged (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="15.[151,255,1670,1694]" captionTargetBox="[181,1402,236,1616]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[172,1426,194,1646]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 2. Cyrta hornei A, fore femur, anterior surface; B, fore femur, dorsal surface; C, fore femur, ventral surface; D, fore tibia, anterior surface; E, fore tibia, dorsal surface; F, fore tibia, ventral surface. G, apex of hind femur, dorsal view; H, base of hind tibia, dorsal surface." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/182578/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
Fig. 
<number box="[151,167,432,458]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
C). Fore tibia with AD and PD seta short to very long, irregularly arranged (
<figureCitation box="[1069,1145,432,458]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="15.[151,255,1670,1694]" captionTargetBox="[181,1402,236,1616]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[172,1426,194,1646]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 2. Cyrta hornei A, fore femur, anterior surface; B, fore femur, dorsal surface; C, fore femur, ventral surface; D, fore tibia, anterior surface; E, fore tibia, dorsal surface; F, fore tibia, ventral surface. G, apex of hind femur, dorsal view; H, base of hind tibia, dorsal surface." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/182578/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
Figs 
<number box="[1130,1145,432,458]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
D, 
<number box="[1181,1197,432,458]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="2.0">2</number>
E); AV and PV setal row extended from base to apex with AV setae relatively short (
<figureCitation box="[908,980,472,498]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="15.[151,255,1670,1694]" captionTargetBox="[181,1402,236,1616]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[172,1426,194,1646]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 2. Cyrta hornei A, fore femur, anterior surface; B, fore femur, dorsal surface; C, fore femur, ventral surface; D, fore tibia, anterior surface; E, fore tibia, dorsal surface; F, fore tibia, ventral surface. G, apex of hind femur, dorsal view; H, base of hind tibia, dorsal surface." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/182578/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
Fig. 
<number box="[964,980,472,498]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
F). 
<collectingCountry box="[1020,1079,472,498]" name="India" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Hind</collectingCountry>
femur slightly broadened distally, with several distal setae elevated on strong bases and several short setae subbasally (
<figureCitation box="[1203,1274,512,538]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="15.[151,255,1670,1694]" captionTargetBox="[181,1402,236,1616]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[172,1426,194,1646]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 2. Cyrta hornei A, fore femur, anterior surface; B, fore femur, dorsal surface; C, fore femur, ventral surface; D, fore tibia, anterior surface; E, fore tibia, dorsal surface; F, fore tibia, ventral surface. G, apex of hind femur, dorsal view; H, base of hind tibia, dorsal surface." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/182578/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
Fig. 
<number box="[1258,1274,512,538]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
G). 
<collectingCountry box="[1318,1377,512,538]" name="India" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Hind</collectingCountry>
tibia flattened and slightly bowed; several supernumeral setae present between AD and PD rows; PD setae very long (
<figureCitation box="[219,290,592,618]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="15.[151,255,1670,1694]" captionTargetBox="[181,1402,236,1616]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[172,1426,194,1646]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 2. Cyrta hornei A, fore femur, anterior surface; B, fore femur, dorsal surface; C, fore femur, ventral surface; D, fore tibia, anterior surface; E, fore tibia, dorsal surface; F, fore tibia, ventral surface. G, apex of hind femur, dorsal view; H, base of hind tibia, dorsal surface." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/182578/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
Fig. 
<number box="[274,290,592,618]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
H).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="3" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,152,1820]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
Male pygofer side moderately long, with macrosetae and short setae near dorsal and apical margin; dorsal margin more or less straight; apical margin broadly or narrowly rounded (
<figureCitation box="[1033,1103,672,698]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="16.[151,255,1541,1565]" captionTargetBox="[202,1390,252,1497]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[163,1439,194,1517]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 3. Cyrta hornei, E-F are after Zhang &amp; Wei (2002). A, male genital capsule, lateral view; B, male genital capsule, dorsal view; C, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; D, connective and style, dorsal view; E, aedeagus, ventral view; F, style, connective and aedeagus, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/182579/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
Fig. 
<number box="[1089,1103,672,698]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
A); inner process present or absent (
<figureCitation box="[243,318,712,738]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="16.[151,255,1541,1565]" captionTargetBox="[202,1390,252,1497]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[163,1439,194,1517]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 3. Cyrta hornei, E-F are after Zhang &amp; Wei (2002). A, male genital capsule, lateral view; B, male genital capsule, dorsal view; C, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; D, connective and style, dorsal view; E, aedeagus, ventral view; F, style, connective and aedeagus, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/182579/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
Figs 
<number box="[304,318,712,738]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
A, 
<number box="[356,370,712,738]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="9.0">9</number>
F, G); posterior interconnecting membrane with weakly developed sclerotised areas comprising a long medial area (dorsal connective) between dorsal apodeme of aedeagus and Xth segment (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="14.[151,255,1718,1742]" captionTargetBox="[200,1387,311,1657]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[167,1413,277,1692]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 1. Cyrta hirsuta A, head and thorax, dorsal view; B, face; C, connective and aedeagus, lateral view; D, male genital capsule, lateral view; E, style and connective, dorsal view; F, apex of aedeagus, ventral view; G, valve and style, ventral view; H, base of aedeagus and dorsal connective, anteroventral view; I, male genital capsule, dorsal view; J, aedeagus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/182577/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
Figs 
<number box="[151,162,792,818]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
C, H). Valve large, posterior margin roundly or angularly produced distally in ventral view (
<figureCitation box="[1282,1355,792,818]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="14.[151,255,1718,1742]" captionTargetBox="[200,1387,311,1657]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[167,1413,277,1692]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 1. Cyrta hirsuta A, head and thorax, dorsal view; B, face; C, connective and aedeagus, lateral view; D, male genital capsule, lateral view; E, style and connective, dorsal view; F, apex of aedeagus, ventral view; G, valve and style, ventral view; H, base of aedeagus and dorsal connective, anteroventral view; I, male genital capsule, dorsal view; J, aedeagus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/182577/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
Figs 
<number box="[1344,1355,792,818]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
D, G). Subgenital plate subtriangular, extending near or slightly beyond apex of pygofer, several short to moderately long setae on ventral surface (
<figureCitation box="[516,589,872,898]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="14.[151,255,1718,1742]" captionTargetBox="[200,1387,311,1657]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[167,1413,277,1692]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 1. Cyrta hirsuta A, head and thorax, dorsal view; B, face; C, connective and aedeagus, lateral view; D, male genital capsule, lateral view; E, style and connective, dorsal view; F, apex of aedeagus, ventral view; G, valve and style, ventral view; H, base of aedeagus and dorsal connective, anteroventral view; I, male genital capsule, dorsal view; J, aedeagus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/182577/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
Figs 
<number box="[578,589,872,898]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
D, G); not fused, or fused basally to each other or to valve (
<figureCitation box="[1329,1403,872,898]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="22.[151,255,1703,1727]" captionTargetBox="[200,1394,225,1642]" captionTargetId="figure@22.[173,1424,194,1679]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 9. Cyrta coalita sp. n. A, head and thorax, dorsal view; B, face; C, aedeagus, ventral view; D, style and connective, dorsal view; E, style, connective and aedeagus, lateral view; F, male genital capsule, ventral view; G, male genital capsule, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/182585/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
Fig. 
<number box="[1387,1403,872,898]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="9.0">9</number>
</figureCitation>
F); sometimes with a sclerotised band medially basally articulated with style (
<figureCitation box="[1028,1098,912,938]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="16.[151,255,1541,1565]" captionTargetBox="[202,1390,252,1497]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[163,1439,194,1517]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 3. Cyrta hornei, E-F are after Zhang &amp; Wei (2002). A, male genital capsule, lateral view; B, male genital capsule, dorsal view; C, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; D, connective and style, dorsal view; E, aedeagus, ventral view; F, style, connective and aedeagus, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/182579/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
Fig. 
<number box="[1083,1098,912,938]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
C). Connective somewhat Tshaped; stem very long, well sclerotised medially, membranous laterally; arms strong (
<figureCitation box="[1166,1236,952,978]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="14.[151,255,1718,1742]" captionTargetBox="[200,1387,311,1657]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[167,1413,277,1692]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 1. Cyrta hirsuta A, head and thorax, dorsal view; B, face; C, connective and aedeagus, lateral view; D, male genital capsule, lateral view; E, style and connective, dorsal view; F, apex of aedeagus, ventral view; G, valve and style, ventral view; H, base of aedeagus and dorsal connective, anteroventral view; I, male genital capsule, dorsal view; J, aedeagus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/182577/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
Figs 
<number box="[1225,1236,952,978]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
C, E). Style with inner basal arm short, outer basal arm elongate; preapical lobe slightly developed with several setae adjacent to apical process; apical process long, extending near to apex of connective, abruptly or slightly expanded and crenulate subbsally, thereafter evenly tapered to apex (
<figureCitation box="[784,849,1072,1098]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="14.[151,255,1718,1742]" captionTargetBox="[200,1387,311,1657]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[167,1413,277,1692]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 1. Cyrta hirsuta A, head and thorax, dorsal view; B, face; C, connective and aedeagus, lateral view; D, male genital capsule, lateral view; E, style and connective, dorsal view; F, apex of aedeagus, ventral view; G, valve and style, ventral view; H, base of aedeagus and dorsal connective, anteroventral view; I, male genital capsule, dorsal view; J, aedeagus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/182577/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
Fig. 
<number box="[838,849,1072,1098]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
E). Aedeagus simple, with shaft moderately broad and long in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[444,510,1112,1138]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="14.[151,255,1718,1742]" captionTargetBox="[200,1387,311,1657]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[167,1413,277,1692]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 1. Cyrta hirsuta A, head and thorax, dorsal view; B, face; C, connective and aedeagus, lateral view; D, male genital capsule, lateral view; E, style and connective, dorsal view; F, apex of aedeagus, ventral view; G, valve and style, ventral view; H, base of aedeagus and dorsal connective, anteroventral view; I, male genital capsule, dorsal view; J, aedeagus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/182577/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
Fig. 
<number box="[499,510,1112,1138]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
C), rarely with a pair of lateral processes (
<figureCitation box="[1007,1077,1112,1138]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="18.[151,255,1625,1649]" captionTargetBox="[200,1393,228,1571]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[177,1418,194,1601]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURE 5. Cyrta orientalis A, aedeagus, ventral view; B, style and connective, dorsal view; C, male genital capsule, lateral view; D, face; E, head and thorax, dorsal view; F, male genital capsule, ventral view; G, style, connective and aedeagus, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/182581/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
Fig. 
<number box="[1062,1077,1112,1138]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
A); basal apodeme well developed, connected with dorsal connective; gonopore apical (
<figureCitation box="[833,900,1152,1178]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="14.[151,255,1718,1742]" captionTargetBox="[200,1387,311,1657]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[167,1413,277,1692]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 1. Cyrta hirsuta A, head and thorax, dorsal view; B, face; C, connective and aedeagus, lateral view; D, male genital capsule, lateral view; E, style and connective, dorsal view; F, apex of aedeagus, ventral view; G, valve and style, ventral view; H, base of aedeagus and dorsal connective, anteroventral view; I, male genital capsule, dorsal view; J, aedeagus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/182577/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
Fig. 
<number box="[888,900,1152,1178]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
C). Xth segment large, elongate (
<figureCitation box="[1291,1357,1152,1178]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="14.[151,255,1718,1742]" captionTargetBox="[200,1387,311,1657]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[167,1413,277,1692]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 1. Cyrta hirsuta A, head and thorax, dorsal view; B, face; C, connective and aedeagus, lateral view; D, male genital capsule, lateral view; E, style and connective, dorsal view; F, apex of aedeagus, ventral view; G, valve and style, ventral view; H, base of aedeagus and dorsal connective, anteroventral view; I, male genital capsule, dorsal view; J, aedeagus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/182577/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
Fig. 
<date box="[1345,1357,1152,1178]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
<number box="[1345,1357,1152,1178]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="1.0">1</number>
</date>
</figureCitation>
I).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,152,1820]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
Female 
<number box="[292,306,1194,1220]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="7.0">7</number>
th sternite much longer than 
<number box="[636,651,1194,1220]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="6.0">6</number>
th sternite; posterior margin roundly convex laterally, strongly concave medially (
<figureCitation box="[329,399,1234,1260]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="17.[151,255,1787,1811]" captionTargetBox="[189,1383,231,1728]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[164,1418,194,1763]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 4. Cyrta horne i A, female genital capsule, lateral view; B, first valvula and detail of sculptures of first valvula; C, apex of female abdomen, ventral view; D, second valvula and detail of sculptures of second valvula; E, third valvula." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/182580/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
Fig. 
<number box="[383,399,1234,1260]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
C). Female pygofer with ventroposterior margin incurved (
<figureCitation box="[1084,1154,1234,1260]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="17.[151,255,1787,1811]" captionTargetBox="[189,1383,231,1728]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[164,1418,194,1763]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 4. Cyrta horne i A, female genital capsule, lateral view; B, first valvula and detail of sculptures of first valvula; C, apex of female abdomen, ventral view; D, second valvula and detail of sculptures of second valvula; E, third valvula." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/182580/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
Fig. 
<number box="[1138,1154,1234,1260]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
A). First valvulae sculpture scale-like, comprising striations, aligned longitudinally basally and oblique distally (
<figureCitation box="[1229,1305,1274,1300]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="17.[151,255,1787,1811]" captionTargetBox="[189,1383,231,1728]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[164,1418,194,1763]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 4. Cyrta horne i A, female genital capsule, lateral view; B, first valvula and detail of sculptures of first valvula; C, apex of female abdomen, ventral view; D, second valvula and detail of sculptures of second valvula; E, third valvula." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/182580/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
Fig. 
<number box="[1288,1305,1274,1300]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
B). Second valvulae with blade-like area extending over distal half, with teeth somewhat fine and the dorsal margin of teeth finely serrate, dorsal sclerotised and hyaline areas present (
<figureCitation box="[902,972,1354,1380]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="17.[151,255,1787,1811]" captionTargetBox="[189,1383,231,1728]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[164,1418,194,1763]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 4. Cyrta horne i A, female genital capsule, lateral view; B, first valvula and detail of sculptures of first valvula; C, apex of female abdomen, ventral view; D, second valvula and detail of sculptures of second valvula; E, third valvula." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/182580/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
Fig. 
<number box="[956,972,1354,1380]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
D). Third valvulae with expanded distal region extending over distal half (
<figureCitation box="[547,618,1394,1420]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="17.[151,255,1787,1811]" captionTargetBox="[189,1383,231,1728]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[164,1418,194,1763]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 4. Cyrta horne i A, female genital capsule, lateral view; B, first valvula and detail of sculptures of first valvula; C, apex of female abdomen, ventral view; D, second valvula and detail of sculptures of second valvula; E, third valvula." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/182580/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
Fig. 
<number box="[602,618,1394,1420]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
E).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
