<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="3" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,152,1820]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,318,1474,1500]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Remarks.</emphasis>
Based on an examination of the 
<typeStatus box="[702,753,1474,1500]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">type</typeStatus>
of its 
<typeStatus box="[825,876,1474,1500]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">type</typeStatus>
species (
<taxonomicName box="[984,1101,1475,1500]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Cyrta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hirsuta">
<emphasis box="[984,1101,1475,1500]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">C. hirsuta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and other species, the identity of 
<taxonomicName box="[229,296,1515,1540]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Cyrta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[229,296,1515,1540]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Cyrta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is revised and the genus is found to be a senior synonym of 
<taxonomicName box="[1003,1106,1515,1540]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Placidus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1003,1106,1515,1540]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Placidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see also Discussion - Identity of Evansâ€™s 
<taxonomicName box="[327,513,1555,1580]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Placidus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hornei">
<emphasis box="[327,513,1555,1580]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Placidus hornei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and, with the exception of its 
<typeStatus box="[876,926,1554,1580]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">type</typeStatus>
species, all other species previously placed in 
<taxonomicName box="[183,250,1595,1620]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Cyrta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[183,250,1595,1620]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Cyrta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see Zhang 
<emphasis box="[402,463,1595,1620]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">et al.</emphasis>
<number box="[472,533,1594,1620]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="2002.0">2002</number>
) belong to a new genus (
<taxonomicName box="[842,961,1595,1620]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Paracyrta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[842,961,1595,1620]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Paracyrta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), described below. 
<taxonomicName box="[1196,1263,1595,1620]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Cyrta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1196,1263,1595,1620]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Cyrta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from 
<emphasis box="[320,379,1635,1660]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Para</emphasis>
c 
<emphasis box="[391,438,1635,1660]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">yrta</emphasis>
by its uniformly coloured pronotum, the presence of tufts of hairlike setae on the scutellum, the longer setae on the tibia, the shorter male pygofer and the longer apical extension of the style apical process. One new species of 
<taxonomicName box="[579,646,1715,1740]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Cyrta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[579,646,1715,1740]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Cyrta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName box="[665,854,1715,1740]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Cyrta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="conduplicata">
<emphasis box="[665,854,1715,1740]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">C. conduplicata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) is the first species of the genus to be described from the Pacific (Sabah). Two species previously placed in 
<taxonomicName box="[846,948,1755,1780]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Placidus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[846,948,1755,1780]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Placidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Li &amp; Zhang 2006" authorityName="Li &amp; Zhang" authorityYear="2006" box="[963,1387,1754,1780]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Placidus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leucomaculatus">
<emphasis box="[963,978,1755,1780]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[992,1176,1755,1780]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">leucomaculatus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Li" box="[1183,1387,1754,1780]" pageId="2" pageNumber="13" refString="Li, Z. Z. &amp; Zhang, B. (2006) Description of three new species of the genus Placidus Distant from China (Hemiptera, Cidadellidae). Acta Zootaxonomica Sinica, 32, 155 - 159 (In Chinese with English abstract)" type="journal article" year="2006">
Li &amp; Zhang 
<number box="[1328,1387,1754,1780]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="2006.0">2006</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis box="[151,295,1795,1820]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">P. m a c u l a t e s</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Li" box="[306,510,1794,1820]" pageId="2" pageNumber="13" refString="Li, Z. Z., Zhang, B. &amp; Wang Y. J. (2007) Cicadellidae: Hecalinae, Coelidiinae, Iassinae. Nirvaninae, Evacanthinae, Escelinae, Hylicinae and Ulopinae. In: Li, Z. Z., Yang, M. F. &amp; Jin, D. C. (eds) Insects From Leigongshan Landscape. Guizhou Science and Technology Publishing House, Guiyang, 759 pp." type="book" year="2007">
Li &amp; Zhang 
<number box="[451,510,1794,1820]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="2007.0">2007</number>
</bibRefCitation>
(in 
<bibRefCitation author="Li" box="[557,719,1794,1820]" pageId="2" pageNumber="13" refString="Li, Z. Z., Zhang, B. &amp; Wang Y. J. (2007) Cicadellidae: Hecalinae, Coelidiinae, Iassinae. Nirvaninae, Evacanthinae, Escelinae, Hylicinae and Ulopinae. In: Li, Z. Z., Yang, M. F. &amp; Jin, D. C. (eds) Insects From Leigongshan Landscape. Guizhou Science and Technology Publishing House, Guiyang, 759 pp." type="book" year="2007">
Li 
<emphasis box="[590,649,1795,1820]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">et al.</emphasis>
<number box="[656,719,1794,1820]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="2007.0">2007</number>
</bibRefCitation>
), belong to another new genus (Wei 
<emphasis box="[1147,1206,1795,1820]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">et al.</emphasis>
in press).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
